children.text: The rendered wall has been constructed visibly out of plumb, which looks poorly finished.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances clause 9.01 Verticality or plumbness of internal and external wall surfaces, states that
‘Wall surfaces are defective if they deviate from vertical by more than 5 mm over a 1.8m straight edge. Refer to Diagram E on page 13 of this Guide’.
This area will need to be re-plumbed into the correct position and re-rendered in accordance with the above.
